# Development Best Practices

## Code Style

- Follow Dart/Flutter style guide
- Use `flutter_lints` package for code quality
- Run `flutter analyze` before committing
- Use meaningful variable and function names

## Performance

- Use `const` constructors when possible
- Implement proper `dispose()` methods in providers
- Use `ListView.builder` for long lists
- Avoid unnecessary rebuilds with proper provider usage

## Error Handling

- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use try-catch blocks for async operations
- Provide meaningful error messages to users
- Log errors for debugging purposes

## Dependencies

- Keep dependencies up to date
- Use specific version constraints in [pubspec.yaml](mdc:pubspec.yaml)
- Avoid adding unnecessary packages
- Document why each dependency is needed

## Asset Management

- Store images in `assets/` directory
- Use appropriate image formats (PNG for icons, JPG for photos)
- Optimize images for mobile devices
- Follow the established asset naming conventions

## Platform Considerations

- Test on both iOS and Android
- Handle platform-specific differences
- Use platform-appropriate widgets when needed
- Consider different screen sizes and densities

## Security

- Store sensitive data in secure storage
- Validate all user inputs
- Use HTTPS for API calls
- Implement proper authentication flows
